This paper deals with index coding, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses linear codes, which could place it in cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
